BCM BFH (hammer forged barrel) LIGHTWEIGHT midlength gas upper receiver group. No BCG or charging handle. Upper is brand new and has never been mated to a lower. If you want higher resolution pics, just let me know. No trades.

For those not familiar with the different barrel profiles, the lightweight barrel reduces a bit of muzzle-end weight (where you want to reduce weight - i.e., the part of the rifle farthest from your body) relative to the government profile barrel. From the chamber to the FSB, the barrel is identical to the government profile barrel. All the weight savings is at the muzzle end.

The streaks and unevenness you see is just the preservative oil that is slathered on at the factory.

I can ship for $25 to nearby states. If you're west of the Mississippi it might be a couple of bucks more, but no more than $30 to lower 48 states.

title: For Sale:  Romanian PSL 7.62x54R with THREE scopes
postcontent:
Up for sale is a PSL semi-automatic rifle. Chambered for the powerful 7.62x54 cartridge. This weapon was designed to engage targets that were out of range for the standard infantry rifle. The action is piston driven Kalashnikov like an AK-47, just scaled up for the heavier cartridge. 

The rifle is in in good condition. Has been cleaned after every time at the range. I have put 80 rounds through it. 

Included is the following:
-Romanian PSL rifle
-4x24T black military scope with illuminated crosshairs with cover and eye piece *RARE
-6x24T black military scope with illuminated crosshairs with cover and eye piece *RARE
-8x42BA grey scope with illuminated crosshairs and bullet drop compensation with cover and eye piece
-1 10 round magazine
-1 5 round magazine
-Sling
-9-11" detachable Bipod

No ammo is included. 

The scopes are all made at the factory in Belarus and have a light for illuminating the reticule. Optics best buy is offering the 8x42 here although they are sold out right now:   http://www.opticsbestbuy.com/POSP-Scope-8x42.html  They are offering it alone for $230 but most that I have seen even used go for closer to the $350 retail price. You can see from the pics that I sent you previously that it has the detachable rubber eye piece. It is the lighter grey "civilian export model" that was attached to the rifle. The 4x and 6x also have illuminated reticules but they differ from the pic I sent of the 8x reticule in that they only have the crosshair at center and the bottom post and 1 crowsfoot and there is only a rangefinder in the 8x. Windage and elevation are click adjustable on the appropriate turrets. The 4 and 6x scopes are the black painted "military" ones thatwere not meant for export. 

As far as how it shoots with the "silver tip" light ball ammo it shoots less than 1 moa and the recoil is about the same as any other 30 cal. I have not shot any of the copper stuff but I know other people who have shot it from theirs and they were getting about 2.5 moa. I have shot brown bear and silver bear ammo as well and that is about 1.5 moa.

Cash only
